CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper May 11, 1957, pg. A19, reads: "Women's Friendly Club - The Women's Friendly Club of Rodman Street Baptist Church is sponsoring its annual fashion show, May 24, 8 o'clock at the church, 6111 Rodman St. Mary Dee, disc jockey of Baltimore, Md., and former Pittsburgher, will fly here to be the commentator. One of the special features will be the clothes of yesteryear. There will also be other scenes to please everyone young or old, male or female. The Rev. S. A. Thurston is minister. Mrs. Estella Allen is present of the club; Mrs. Gladys Cralle is chairman, Miss Dorothy Updyke, co-chairman, and Mrs. Catharine Frazier, vice president. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of eighteen women wearing hats, members of Women's Friendly Club of Rodman Street Baptist Church, posed behind table planning fashion show, in Rodman Street Baptist Church
